ivalent about fundamentally inexpensive high quality companies in more prosaic businesses the true connoisseurs of valuecorporate acquirers and leveraged buyout groupsare aggressively taking advantage of the attractive merchandise in the markets discount bin and of course value investors like us call this our space the abc funds conservative portfolio mix of undervalued equities us treasury securities and risk arbitrage investments helped it to a respectable  return this quarter and an impressive  gain for the first six months of  investment results a  quarter  st nd rd th year       net asset value       total return         net asset value       total return         net asset value       total return         net asset value       total return         net asset value       total return         net asset value       total return         net asset value       total return         net asset value       total return   b   b  dividend history payment ex date rate per share reinvestment price    december      december      december     december      september      december      december      december     average annual returns  june   a  year    year   life of fund b    a total returns and average annual returns reflect changes in share price and reinvestment of dividends and are net of expenses the net asset value of the fund is reduced on the exdividend payment date by the amount of the dividend paid of course returns represent past performance and do not guarantee future results investment returns and the principal value of an investment will fluctuate when shares are redeemed they may be worth more or less than their original cost b from commencement of investment operations on may   investment performance for the second quarter ended june   the gabelli abc funds the fund total return was  the lipper us treasury money market average had a total return of  over the same period the lipper average reflects the average performance of mutual funds classified in this parti